article.headline: Oklahoma 63, Texas A&M 51
article.story:
COLLEGE STATION, Texas (AP) -- Leah Rush scored 26 points to lead
Oklahoma to a 63-51 victory over Texas A&M on Saturday night.

Rush hit 13-of-17 from the field. She also pulled down eight
rebounds. Laura Andrews scored 15 points and added 10 rebounds
while Dionnah Jackson had 15 rebounds, 16 assists and two blocked
shots.

Oklahoma (11-5, 3-2 Big 12) led 35-28 at the half.

Morenike Atunrase led Texas A&M (11-5, 2-4) with 16 points.
Erica Roy added 10.

The Sooners shot 53 percent from the field while Texas A&M shot
only 30 percent.
